						Schwab Charles Investment Management Inc. Raises Position in Steven Madden, Ltd. (NASDAQ:SHOO)					

						 July 18th, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Tyrone Williams 


							Filed Under: Finance - SEC Filing Articles 







Tweet










Schwab Charles Investment Management Inc. raised its position in shares of  Steven Madden, Ltd. (NASDAQ:SHOO) by 7.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor  owned 350,321 shares of the textile maker’s stock after buying an additional 24,820 shares during the period. Schwab Charles Investment Management Inc.’s holdings in Steven Madden were worth $13,505,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
A number of other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in SHOO. Russell Investments Group Ltd. acquired a new position in  Steven Madden during the fourth quarter worth $2,246,000.  Envestnet Asset Management Inc. increased its position in  Steven Madden by 15.1% in the fourth quarter. Envestnet Asset Management Inc. now owns 5,823 shares of the textile maker’s stock worth $208,000 after buying an additional 765 shares during the period.  Two Sigma Investments LP acquired a new position in  Steven Madden during the fourth quarter worth $1,531,000.  Tudor Investment Corp Et Al acquired a new position in  Steven Madden during the fourth quarter worth $204,000.  Finally, Norges Bank acquired a new position in  Steven Madden during the fourth quarter worth $26,293,000. 92.82% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 
Shares of Steven Madden, Ltd. (NASDAQ:SHOO) opened at 39.00 on Tuesday. Steven Madden, Ltd. has a 1-year low of $32.30 and a 1-year high of $40.75. The firm has a market cap of $2.32 billion, a PE ratio of 19.55 and a beta of 0.54. The stock’s 50 day moving average is $38.44 and its 200-day moving average is $37.26. 




Steven Madden (NASDAQ:SHOO) last posted its earnings results on Friday, April 21st. The textile maker reported $0.47 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.43 by $0.04. Steven Madden had a net margin of 8.17% and a return on equity of 17.17%. The firm had revenue of $366.40 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $359.52 million. During the same quarter in the prior year, the business posted $0.33 EPS. The business’s revenue was up 11.2% compared to the same quarter last year.  Analysts expect that  Steven Madden, Ltd. will post $2.19 earnings per share for the current year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: “Schwab Charles Investment Management Inc. Raises Position in Steven Madden, Ltd. (NASDAQ:SHOO)” was first  published by Daily Political and is the sole property of of Daily Political. If you are reading this report on another domain, it was copied illegally and reposted in violation of US and international copyright laws. The correct version of this report can be accessed at https://www.dailypolitical.com/2017/07/18/schwab-charles-investment-management-inc-raises-position-in-steven-madden-ltd-nasdaqshoo.html. 
SHOO has been the subject of a number of analyst reports. Jefferies Group LLC  reaffirmed a “hold” rating and issued a $37.00 target price on shares of Steven Madden in a research report on Monday, April 3rd. Susquehanna Bancshares Inc  reissued a “positive” rating and issued a $42.00 price objective on shares of Steven Madden in a research report on Monday, April 17th. Zacks Investment Research downgraded shares of Steven Madden from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report on Wednesday, April 19th. Canaccord Genuity  reissued a “buy” rating and issued a $45.00 price objective on shares of Steven Madden in a research report on Wednesday, April 19th. Finally, Piper Jaffray Companies  set a $41.00 price objective on shares of Steven Madden and gave the company a “buy” rating in a research report on Friday, April 21st. Four equities research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and eight have issued  a buy rating to the stock. The company presently has an average rating of “Buy” and a consensus target price of $41.18.
In related news, CFO Arvind Dharia sold 20,000 shares of the stock in a transaction dated Monday, June 12th. The shares were sold at an average price of $40.22, for a total transaction of $804,400.00. Following the completion of the transaction, the chief financial officer now owns 66,662 shares in the company, valued at $2,681,145.64. The transaction was disclosed in a document filed with the SEC, which is available through this link. Also, insider Karla Frieders sold 5,000 shares of the stock in a transaction dated Monday, June 19th. The shares were sold at an average price of $38.61, for a total transaction of $193,050.00. Following the transaction, the insider now owns 83,216 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $3,212,969.76. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. In the last 90 days, insiders have sold 125,194 shares of company stock valued at $4,927,107. 2.20% of the stock is owned by company insiders. 
Steven Madden Company Profile
Steven Madden, Ltd. and its subsidiaries design, source, market and sell name brand and private label footwear for women, men and children, and name brand and private label fashion handbags and accessories. The Company operates through five segments: Wholesale Footwear, Wholesale Accessories, Retail, First Cost and Licensing.
